# Tickets, Lanes & Gates

Source: **`docs/planning/implementation-tickets.md`**

## Parallel spool (mandatory)

Nathan **always** launches all parallel-safe tickets in the current wave **at the same time** — one **Task subagent** per ticket, prefer different lanes. **Never claim "spooled" without calling the Task tool.**

## Lane agents — do NOT commit/push/build

1. Read ticket + spec Q## + expert from `.cursor/experts.md`
2. Implement in lane files only
3. Verify: `git status`, `git diff --stat`, `git diff` — **must be non-empty**
4. Read changed files; run **`npm test` (full suite, all green)** + lint/typecheck — not `npm run build`
5. Hand off to Nathan with diff output + expert alignment

**Forbidden for lane agents:** `git commit`, `git push`, `npm run build`, marking ticket DONE.

## Nathan — wave close + auto-advance

Verify all handoffs → **full test suite green** → build → **one commit + one push per wave** → mark DONE → **spool next wave immediately** (`07-wave-auto-advance.mdc`).

